        conseils: "Saint-Corentin Cathedral is an absolute jewel: its 15th-century stained glass and off-axis nave make it unique in France — the visit is free and takes 30 minutes. The Quimper Faience Museum (Locmaria quarter, 5 euros) traces three centuries of Quimper pottery with exceptional pieces. The Henriot-Quimper shop (Rue Haute) sells authentic hand-painted faience — the quintessential Breton souvenir. The pedestrian streets of the centre (Rue Kereon, Rue du Salle, Rue des Gentilshommes) are ideal for strolling between creperies and shops. The covered Halles Saint-Francois market (every morning except Sunday) offers seafood, Cornouaille AOC cider and kouign-amann, the iconic buttery pastry born in nearby Douarnenez. The Jardin de la Retraite behind the cathedral offers an exotic green haven with palm trees and camellias.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The TER Vannes — Quimper costs about €25 and takes 1h20 to 1h50 depending on stops (with possible connection at Lorient). Frequency is modest: roughly one direct train every 2h. The BreizhGo bus links both cities for about €12 in 2h30. BlaBlaCar offers rides from €9. The TaxiNeo taxi at €125 — €160 provides a direct door-to-door journey with no connections. For 3-4 passengers, the cost works out to €31-53 per person, justified by comfort and time savings, especially with luggage.",
